column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Beautiful clear day.  Other than minor surface pollen close to shore-great.  Ducks + a loon on the lake today.
Beautiful day.  Green slime (is this algae ) starting on west shoreline.  Ducks + a loon on the lake today.  Three blue heron on NW bog.
Hot humid weather.  Received heavy rain about 2 days prior to reading.  Loon- ducks + blue heron still on lake.
Green slime.  Sunny today-had rain for the last 2 days.  Green slime accumulating in many parts of lake now.
Green slime.  Hot humid sunny day.  Received heavy rain early in the morning.  Would like to know what green hairy-like masses are (they are not weeds) .  Many such masses throughout the lake.
Green slime.  Sunny day.  Have had several days of rain since last reading along with windy conditions.  Green airy slime patches throughout the lake.
Public perception due to green slime.  Had heavy rain yesterday.  Still have patches of green slime in the lake.
Public perception due to green slime.  Have had considerable rain + days have been much cooler.
Had rain 2 days ago.  Yesterday was cool + breezy.  Today sunny + warmer.  Not as much slime present.
Green slime or algae almost gone.  Weather cool.
No rain for several days-cold temps.  Green slime going away.  Lake level going down.
Hot sunny day.  No rain for a few days.  Has been warm.
Water becoming murky.  Weather has been cool.  Today sunny- but cool.  About 2 dozen ducks on the lake today.
Last few days the weather has been beautiful-sunny + warm.
Has been warm and humid.  Received heavy rainfall the last 2 days.
Hot- humid-have had thunderstorms rain for 2 days.  Some weeds showing on surface of water.
Except for today- has been cold + rainy.  This will be last reading for season.
Had heavy rain this a.m.  Breezy- no heavy rains.  Ducks are on the lake.
Weather has been cool.  Today it was about 60 degrees and partly sunny.
Public perception due to pollen.  Have had four warm days.  White fluffy pollen- very bad.  Observed start of water lilies on bottom of lake.
Pollen.  Cool temps. the last five days-pollen still very bad.
Pollen.  Very hot weather-today it was 100 degrees.
Pollen.  No rain for over 2 weeks.  Has been very hot + humid.  Today's reading was taken just after rain-overcast-partly cloudy.
Algae starting.  Having a cold spell.  No significant rainfall lately.  This reading was in participation of national "secchi dip-in".
Algae present.  In a hot humid spell-no significant rain for quite some time.  Algae is quite evident.
Have had rain + some storms in past week.  Saw blue heron today.  Fewer ducks on lake this year-no babies.
Has been hot/humid for a few days.  Yesterday had thunderstorm.
Hot + humid lately-severe thunderstorms a few days ago.
Have had several thunderstorms lately with heavy rain-high humidity.
Still hot + humid and warm water.
Have had frost + snow about 4 days ago.  This is the last reading for this year.
This was a reading for the great secchi dip-in. clear warm day.
Weather has been cool and rainy for several days.
Has been cool- breezy and rainy for almost 2 weeks.
Most days it's very breezy. had storm with heavy rain a week ago.
Algae only on west side of lake. two clumps of soil floating on water far from shore.  Lake level: very high
Nights have been cool-days are warm but breezy. loon on lake today.
Night are cool but no frost here. leaves are changing.
Partly cloudy- 72 degrees Fahrenheit- slight wind- and water clarity was good.
